Let’s dive into the most exciting, unforgettable, and sometimes surprising things to do in Abu Dhabi – placed into fun categories to help you design the perfect adventure.



Cultural & Iconic Things to Do in Abu Dhabi

If Abu Dhabi had a crown, the Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque would be the jewel in the center. Massive, elegant, and hauntingly beautiful - this is not just a tourist spot; it’s an experience.

The white marble reflects the sun by day and glows gently at night. Inside, you’ll find the world’s largest hand-knotted carpet and one of the most beautiful chandeliers ever created.

And here’s the best part: it’s also one of the things to do in Abu Dhabi for free.

Other must-visit cultural highlights:





Qasr Al Watan (Presidential Palace) – A real-life palace open to the public



Louvre Abu Dhabi – Where ancient history meets modern art



Heritage Village – Experience traditional Emirati life

If you want to understand Abu Dhabi’s soul, this is where you start.



Fun Things to Do in Abu Dhabi – For the Thrill Seekers

Adrenaline lovers, this city is your playground.



Ferrari World on Yas Island - is legendary. Not just for the red Ferrari roof, but for Formula Rossa — the world’s fastest roller coaster, which launches you from 0 to 240 km/h in just seconds.

Other fun things to do in Abu Dhabi that will get your heart racing:





Warner Bros World – Ride with Batman, hang out with Scooby-Doo



Yas Waterworld – Wild slides, wave pools and lazy rivers



SeaWorld Abu Dhabi – A brand-new, immersive marine world



Jet skiing along the Corniche



Skydiving over the desert dunes

When it comes to things to do in Abu Dhabi, boredom simply isn’t part of the vocabulary.



Outdoor Activities in Abu Dhabi – Beaches, Nature & Wildlife



Time to slow down and breathe.

One of the most underrated activities in Abu Dhabi is simply enjoying nature. The city has made a beautiful effort to balance urban life with untouched landscapes.

Must-try outdoor experiences:





Kayaking in the Mangrove National Park
 Paddle through peaceful green tunnels with birds all around you.




Relaxing at Saadiyat Beach
 White sand, turquoise water, hidden turtles.




Exploring Jubail Mangrove Park
 Walk on the wooden boardwalk above the magical wetlands.




Sunset walks on the Corniche
 A long, perfect stretch for biking, jogging, or just watching the sun fall into the ocean.
Many of these experiences also fall under things to do in Abu Dhabi for free, which is perfect for budget travelers.



Desert Magic: Classic Things to Do in Abu Dhabi



You absolutely cannot visit Abu Dhabi without touching the golden dunes.

A desert safari is one of the most iconic things to do in Abu Dhabi. And it feels like something straight out of a movie.

Expect:





Dune bashing in 4x4 vehicles



Sandboarding down golden slopes



Camel rides into the sunset



Traditional BBQ dinner



Fire shows & belly dancing under the stars

If you want a more dramatic version, head to the Liwa Desert, where the dunes are some of the largest in the world.

Few activities in Abu Dhabi will ever give you the same sense of freedom.



Modern City Fun: Shopping & Entertainment

Let’s be honest - shopping is also one of the very real things to do in Abu Dhabi.

But here, it isn’t just about buying things. It’s about the experience.

Top spots:





Yas Mall – Right next to Ferrari World



The Galleria Mall (Al Maryah Island) – Luxury + waterfront views



Marina Mall – Overlooking the skyline of Abu Dhabi



Souk Central Market – Old-school charm mixed with modern luxury

Many malls include games, cinemas, arcades, indoor skydiving, and dining areas that turn a simple visit into one of the more relaxing fun things to do in Abu Dhabi.



Foodie Moment: One of the Tastiest Things to Do in Abu Dhabi

Abu Dhabi’s food scene deserves its own award.

From luxurious fine dining by Michelin star chefs to small street cafés serving up shawarma and karak tea, eating your way through the city is absolutely one of the most delicious things to do in Abu Dhabi.

Must-try experiences:





Arabic breakfast by the sea



Emirati traditional food at local restaurants



Dinner at a rooftop restaurant overlooking the city



Fresh seafood grills



Hidden cafes serving camel milk desserts

Even exploring local food trucks can be one of the most fun and authentic activities in Abu Dhabi.



Things to Do in Abu Dhabi for Free (Yes, Really!)

Traveling on a budget? Abu Dhabi still wins.

Here are amazing things to do in Abu Dhabi for free:





Visit Sheikh Zayed Mosque



Walk the Abu Dhabi Corniche



Enjoy public beaches



Explore Heritage Village



Walk through Al Bateen area



Visit art exhibitions & galleries on special days



Enjoy free cultural festivals

The fact that such a luxury city offers so many things to do in Abu Dhabi for free is one of its most charming surprises.



Night Life & Evening Things to Do in Abu Dhabi

Once the sun sets, Abu Dhabi transforms into a glowing fantasyland.

Want to make it romantic? Adventure? Chill vibes?

Top night-time things to do in Abu Dhabi:





Night kayaking in the mangroves



Sunset at Emirates Palace



Rooftop lounges and shisha cafés



Dhow cruises with music and dinner



City lights photography at Marina & Corniche

The city becomes softer, cooler, and even more magical.



Unique & Hidden Fun Things to Do in Abu Dhabi

Want to tell people you did something different?

Try these less known but incredibly cool fun things to do in Abu Dhabi:

 • Falcon Hospital Tour
 • Horse riding in the desert
 • Camping on Hudayriyat Island
 • Fishing trips at sunrise
 • Photography walks through old neighbourhoods
 • Hot air balloon rides

These are the kinds of activities in Abu Dhabi that turn your trip from good to unforgettable.



Why Abu Dhabi Belongs on Your Bucket List

The real magic of Abu Dhabi isn’t just in its attractions — it’s in its balance.

It gives you:





Ultra-modern architecture 



Deep-rooted traditions 



Wild adventure 



Peaceful nature 



Budget-friendly fun 



World-class luxury 

There are very few cities in the world where you can go from a mosque to a rollercoaster, from the desert to the ocean, from ancient history to futuristic architecture — all in one day.

And that’s exactly why the list of things to do in Abu Dhabi never really ends… it just keeps getting better.



Ready to Explore the Best Things to Do in Abu Dhabi?

Whether you’re a solo traveller, a couple on a romantic getaway, a family with kids, or someone searching for adventure, Abu Dhabi is waiting to surprise you.

With endless things to do in Abu Dhabi, exciting activities in Abu Dhabi, unforgettable fun things to do in Abu Dhabi, and plenty of things to do in Abu Dhabi for free, this city is a full-package destination.

So pack your bags.
Charge your camera.
And get ready to experience one of the most beautiful, exciting and unforgettable destinations in the world.

Abu Dhabi is calling. Will you answer?



