uired from the developer before transferring ownership, especially for resale units. Step 6: Register the Property Complete the registration process with DLD and obtain a title deed in your name. Taxes and Fees for Foreign Buyers One of Dubai’s most attractive features is its tax-free property ownership for foreigners: No property tax No capital gains tax No rental income tax Buyers must only pay a 4% transfer fee to the DLD and agency fees (typically 1 -5%). Can Foreigners Obtain Residency by Buying Property? Yes, property ownership in Dubai makes foreigners eligible for long-term residence visas. Investor Visa Options: 3-Year Visa: Property worth AED 750,000+ 5-Year Visa: Property worth AED 5 million+ 10-Year Golden Visa: Property worth AED 2 million+ (conditions apply) The Abu Dhabi Residents Office also offers golden visas through investments in projects like those by Aldar Properties. To know golden visa guidelines https://u.ae/en/information-and-services/visa-and-emirates-id/residence-visas/golden-visa https://icp.gov.ae/en/golden-residency/ Can Foreigners Own 100% of a Property or Business in Dubai? Absolutely. Foreign nationals can: Own 100% of residential or commercial property in freehold areas. Own 100% of mainland businesses across several sectors (since June 1, 2021) — no Emirati partner required. This major legal reform has contributed to Dubai’s surge in global investor confidence. Why Invest in Dubai Real Estate? 1. Tax-Friendly System Dubai offers a zero-tax environment for property and rental income. 2. Strong ROI Potential Real estate in Dubai offers one of the highest returns globally, especially in high-demand areas. 3. Robust Infrastructure The Dubai Urban Master Plan 2040 and ongoing mega-projects ensure long-term growth. 4. Investor-Friendly Laws 100% property and business ownership, long-term visas, and low fees make Dubai a magnet for investors. FAQs (ADD AS DROPDOWN) Can I Buy Property in Dubai as a Non-Resident? Yes, non-residents can buy