idence-visas/golden-visa https://icp.gov.ae/en/golden-residency/ Dubai Statistics Center - Real Estate Market Performance Reports https://www.dsc.gov.ae/ Dubai Municipality - Dubai 2040 Urban Master Plan https://www.dm.gov.ae/ Additional Useful Resources Real Estate Regulatory Agency (RERA) https://www.rera.ae/ Dubai Pulse - Government Data Portal https://www.dubaipulse.gov.ae/organisation/dld Dubai Investment Development Agency (Dubai FDI) https://www.dubaifdi.gov.ae/ UAE Ministry of Economy <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://www.moec.gov.ae/">https://www.moec.gov.ae/</a> </p>2a:T1ecc,Your Complete Guide to Buy Property in Dubai as a Foreigner Laws & Regulations Last modified : June 2025 Dubai’s real estate market has been booming over the last few decades,thanks to Dubai government’s legalized foreign property ownership in 2002, allowing expats and foreign nationals to own property under specific conditions. It has been attracting both expats and international investors ever since. With robust infrastructure, tax-free policies, and investor-friendly regulations, the Emirate has positioned itself as a global hub for real estate investment. Recognizing this demand, If you're planning to buy a house, apartment, or commercial space in Dubai, this guide outlines the eligibility, legal framework, property types, and step-by-step process. Can Foreigners Buy Property in Dubai? Yes, foreigners, including non-residents and expats residing in the UAE can buy, sell, or lease property in Dubai. Foreign nationals are allowed to purchase: Freehold Properties in designated zones approved by the Dubai Land Department (DLD). Leasehold Properties for a maximum of 99 years. Commercial Properties, provided they have a valid Trade Licence. This applies to both residential and commercial assets. Types of Property Ownership in Dubai for Foreigners Freehold Properties Freehold ownership gives buyers full rights over the property and the land it occupies. F