re transferring ownership, especially for resale units. Step 6: Register the Property Complete the registration process with DLD and obtain a title deed in your name. Taxes and Fees for Foreign Buyers One of Dubai’s most attractive features is its tax-free property ownership for foreigners: No property tax No capital gains tax No rental income tax Buyers must only pay a 4% transfer fee to the DLD and agency fees (typically 1 -5%). Can Foreigners Obtain Residency by Buying Property? Yes, property ownership in Dubai makes foreigners eligible for long-term residence visas. Investor Visa Options: 3-Year Visa: Property worth AED 750,000+ 5-Year Visa: Property worth AED 5 million+ 10-Year Golden Visa: Property worth AED 2 million+ (conditions apply) The Abu Dhabi Residents Office also offers golden visas through investments in projects like those by Aldar Properties. To know golden visa guidelines https://u.ae/en/information-and-services/visa-and-emirates-id/residence-visas/golden-visa https://icp.gov.ae/en/golden-residency/ Can Foreigners Own 100% of a Property or Business in Dubai? Absolutely. Foreign nationals can: Own 100% of residential or commercial property in freehold areas. Own 100% of mainland businesses across several sectors (since June 1, 2021) — no Emirati partner required. This major legal reform has contributed to Dubai’s surge in global investor confidence. Why Invest in Dubai Real Estate? 1. Tax-Friendly System Dubai offers a zero-tax environment for property and rental income. 2. Strong ROI Potential Real estate in Dubai offers one of the highest returns globally, especially in high-demand areas. 3. Robust Infrastructure The Dubai Urban Master Plan 2040 and ongoing mega-projects ensure long-term growth. 4. Investor-Friendly Laws 100% property and business ownership, long-term visas, and low fees make Dubai a magnet for investors. FAQs (ADD AS DROPDOWN) Can I Buy Property in Dubai as a Non-Resident? Yes, non-residents can buy in designated freehold zones like Downtown Dubai, Palm Jumeirah, Dubai Hills Estate ETC. When Did Dubai Allow Foreign Property Ownership? In 2002, Dubai legalized freehold ownership for foreigners, transforming its real estate market. What Is the Minimum Salary to Qualify for a Mortgage in Dubai? AED 10,000–15,000 per month depending on the bank and property type. Is It Worth Buying Property in Dubai? Yes, especially if you're looking for tax-free income, high ROI, and long-term visa eligibility. Final Thoughts Dubai offers opportunities for foreign investors and residents alike. Whether you're looking to live in a modern city with world-class amenities or seeking real estate investment opportunities, buying property in Dubai can be a strategic decision when backed by proper research and professional guidance. Important: This guide is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal, financial, or investment advice. Always consult with qualified professionals before making any property investment decisions. If you're ready to take the next step, browse through (TAG PROPERTYSELLER) to make an informed purchase. Sources and References Dubai Land Department - Historical Overview of Foreign Property Ownership Laws https://dubailand.gov.ae/en/ Dubai Land Department Annual Report 2024 - Foreign Investment Statistics https://dubailand.gov.ae/en/eservices/all-services/ Dubai Law No. 7 of 2006 concerning Real Property Registration in the Emirate of Dubai https://dubailand.gov.ae/en/ UAE Federal Decree-Law No. 26 of 2020 - Foreign Direct Investment Law Official UAE Government Portal: https://u.ae/ UAE Central Bank - Mortgage Lending Guidelines for Foreign Nationals https://www.centralbank.ae/ Dubai Land Department - Official Fee Structure for Property Transactions https://dubailand.gov.ae/en/eservices/all-services/ UAE Federal Authority for Identity and Citizenship - Golden Visa Program Guidelines https://u.ae/en/information-and-services/visa-and-emirates-id/residence-visas/golden-visa http